# Commit Message Style

## Format
Use Conventional Commits:
```
<type>(<scope>): <description>

[optional body]
```

## Types
- `feat`: New feature or capability
- `fix`: Bug fix
- `refactor`: Code restructuring without behavior change
- `docs`: Documentation only
- `test`: Adding or fixing tests
- `chore`: Build config, dependencies, CI
- `perf`: Performance improvement

## Scopes (by crate)
- `cli`: kargo-cli
- `core`: kargo-core
- `ops`: kargo-ops
- `maven`: kargo-maven
- `resolver`: kargo-resolver
- `compiler`: kargo-compiler
- `plugin`: kargo-plugin
- `lint`: kargo-lint
- `toolchain`: kargo-toolchain
- `util`: kargo-util

## Examples
```
feat(core): add flavor and variant types to manifest parsing
fix(maven): handle missing checksum in POM metadata
refactor(resolver): extract conflict resolution into separate module
docs(cli): document --flavor and --variant flags
test(core): add property interpolation edge cases
chore: update workspace dependencies
```
